Twin Cedars Family,

This afternoon Twin Cedars was notified by the Iowa Department of Education that we were approved for the virtual learning waiver. Teachers will begin contacting students tomorrow and the first formal day of online instruction will be on Thursday, August 27th. We will plan to resume with face to face instruction in our buildings on Tuesday, September 8th.

Thank You.

shared_text:
Twin Cedars Elementary
August 12 at 6:13 PM ·

School starts in 1 week, August 19. Please send a visor, baseball cap or a hat with a rim with your PK-6th grade child. We will provide each child with face shield that clips to the hat. Students will be asked to wear face shields only when they are in a small group or student pair. We hope that wearing a hat will make this a "little" fun for the students. Of course, all students are welcome to wear a facial mask or shield at all times and at the request of a parent.

Teachers will wear face shields or facial masks whenever they are within 6 feet of a student (which will be pretty much all the time 😀)

Also, PK-6 rooms will also have desk shields.

We hope to see you on August 17th at your Back to School appointment. It will be a great opportunity to see and hear about what we are doing to keep our kids safe.

Twin Cedars will be providing Chromebooks to 7th-12th grade students for at home and school use in August. We will nearly have enough devices to provide elementary students with computers as well. In the event of another closing, most elementary students would be sent home with a device. Now we need to consider internet access. The Iowa Department of Education is conducting a survey to identify our need. If you have not completed the survey and you have TC students that live with you, please take a few minutes to answer the questions.
https://tinyurl.com/ycd7h3tf
The survey closes next Wednesday. We still have about 50 families that haven't responded. Thank-you!

post_text:
The Career Discovery Network at DMACC has worked to “pivot” their deliverables in order to continue offering some career awareness and exploration opportunities to their area high school students. They are excited to launch their Virtual Career Discovery Sessions starting this Friday, May 8th!

Each Friday going forward, they will host ZOOM calls with local professionals to introduce students career pathways and local businesses. Each session will be conducted through ZOOM, and will be live so students can interact with the presenter and ask questions. They will also record these presentations so they can be viewed at a later time.

Check out the link to view session offerings and register! They will be adding sessions all the time, so make sure to check their website often!

https://www.dmacc.edu/careerdiscovery/Pages/careerdiscovery.aspx

post_text: Please Pass the Love has compiled a list of mental health providers who are doing telehealth AND are accepting new clients! Click on the link for the full list.
shared_text:
Please Pass the Love
April 17 at 4:17 PM ·

We feel your sadness today, too, Iowa. We know how much our educators love their students and vice versa. You have students and families struggling right now, and you may never know about it.

We have compiled a desperately needed and frequently requested list of mental health providers that are doing telehealth AND taking new clients. All schools absolutely need to be posting this list to their websites and sharing with families. They need it and they need you to share it. Hurry and share with your networks, because you do not know who needs it the most right now. Please do not wait for them to come to you. The complete list can be found on our website:

https://www.pleasepassthelove.org/covid-19-resources

post_text: Check out Nurse Joni's new Facebook page!
shared_text:
Twin Cedars School Nurse
April 12 at 5:48 PM ·

Hey all! I know we are living in a crazy time right now and I wanted to make it easier for everyone to contact me (if needed) and for me to provide information and resources to everyone!

Since I'm new to TC I just thought I would introduce myself! I'm Joni Hannon the TC school nurse. I joined the TC family in December! I have been a nurse for 12 years and prior to coming to TC I was a surgery nurse at PRHC for 10 years and before that I was a Med/Surg nurse there. I'm a mom of 3, my oldest Easton is 9 and I have twins Liam and Kella who are 4. My husband Brad is an engineer for Musco. Outside of work I love to run and be outside with my family!

I hope you are all doing well. I am certainly missing all of our students and staff and can't wait til we can get back to school. If you having any questions or need anything please feel free to reach out to me!

Nurse Joni

March 19 at 6:08 AM ·

Tweens & Teens!
Join us for our very first Virtual Live-Stream T[w]EEN Yoga class TONIGHT at 5pm for FREE! 💥
We know that you are isolated at home probably feeling a little worried and bored. We will help ease your worries and anxiety, move, talk, laugh, and relax. Ask your friends to join us too! Anyone can come from around the world 🌎
Head over to our website (in comments) and register to get your Zoom link and password. See you tonight! ✌🏼

post_text: Check out this awesome local resource!
shared_text:
Mahaska County Conservation
March 18 at 9:14 AM ·

Beginning Monday at 10:30 am, go to Mahaska County Conservation on Facebook to watch “Nature Live” with Ranger Laura. She will create live videos to teach and connect people with nature and science. There will be a new topic every day Monday through Friday. Share your topic ideas below, but please know our resources are limited at this time. If supplies are needed from home, the list will be posted the day before. If you happen to miss one, they will be saved on Facebook.

MCCB wants to continue to connect with everyone through these live videos. So get ready for outdoor activities, science experiments, fun crafts and more. Let’s meet up on Monday at 10:30 am!

post_text: Update for anyone who signed up for the April ACT test date.
shared_text:
ACT Student
March 16 at 10:10 AM ·

The safety of students and test center staff is our top priority. We have rescheduled the April 4 national test date across the U.S. in response to concerns about the spread of the coronavirus (COVID-19).

All students registered for the April 4 test date will receive an email in the next few days informing them of the postponement and instructions for free rescheduling to June 13 or a future national test date.

More information: https://bit.ly/2QjSC3n
